Introduction

BSS, also known as BooSeokSoon, is a special unit of SEVENTEEN under Pledis Entertainment. The group consists of Seungkwan (Boo Seungkwan), DK (Lee Seokmin), and Hoshi (Kwon Soonyoung). They made their official debut with the digital single "Just Do It" on March 21, 2018.

On February 6, 2023, BSS made their first comeback with their 1st single album "SECOND WIND" with the title track "Fighting (Feat. Lee Youngji)" which became a smash hit proceeding to win multiple awards such as their first win as a sub-unit on February 15, 2023, at Show Champion and more on music shows. The song also won the Performance of the Year Grand Prize (Daesang) at the 2023 Asia Artist Awards.

Following such success, the sub-unit became part of the OST playlist for the new tvN drama ‘Queen of Tears’ starring Kim Soo-Hyun and Kim Ji-won with the song titled "The Reasons of My Smiles" on March 10, 2024.
